latestPosts.caption:
From Serving Guests to Shapping Teams: My 14 Years of Journey with Emaar Hospitality Group 

Fourteen years ago, I walked into Emaar Hospitality Group as a Waiter—eager, driven, and determined to make a mark. What began as a role on the service floor soon evolved into a lifelong passion for hospitality and people development.

In those early days, I learned the true meaning of service: attention to detail, empathy, resilience, and the power of creating memorable guest experiences. But more importantly, I observed the power of teamwork, leadership, and the impact that great people practices can have on individuals and organizations alike.

It was this insight that sparked my interest in Human Resources. With every opportunity I was given, I leaned in—volunteering for internal initiatives, supporting team engagement programs, and studying HR fundamentals outside of working hours. My leaders noticed my commitment, and I was given a chance to transition into an entry-level HR role.

From there, the climb was both challenging and rewarding. I immersed myself in talent acquisition, employee relations, learning and development, and HR operations. I learned from some of the best minds in the industry and gradually took on more responsibility—eventually growing into a senior HR leadership role.

Today, I lead with the same humility I had when I first started—grounded in empathy and driven by purpose. My background in frontline operations allows me to connect authentically with colleagues at every level, ensuring that our HR strategies are not only aligned with business goals but also rooted in the real experiences of our teams.

I am grateful to Emaar for being more than just an employer—it has been a school, a mentor, and a platform that allowed me to transform a job into a meaningful career.
